  <h1>
   layer_get_all
  </h1>
  This function will return an
  <a href="../../../../GML_Overview/Arrays.htm">
   array
  </a>
  populated with the unique ID values of each layer in the room.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">layer_get_all()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Arrays.htm">
 Array
</a>
(populated with Layer IDs)
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var a = layer_get_all();
for (var i = 0; i &amp;amp;lt; array_length(a); i++;)
{
    layer_destroy(a[i]);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code retrieves all the layers in a room and adds their ID values to an array. This array is then parsed to destroy or the room layers.
 </body>
